bug.short_desc: Warnings in the API viewer are missing

long_desc.thetext: I had the case that the documentation of a constructor parameter was missing but the API-viewer did not mark the class with a warning in the tree view.
Created attachment 617 Screenshot of the api-viewer

Its getting even worse. It only happens if the parameter is also available in a superclass and is not documented there. If you document the parameter in the superclass, the documentation will be mirrored to the subclass, which is ok. But if you have an undocumented additional parameter in the subclass, both documentations are missing.

In the first case (as seen in the screenshot), the generator marks the derived class' constructor with an error since it has an undocumented parameter, but later the superclass constructor is checked for a parameter with the same name. Since that exists, the generator removes the error from the derived class. The comments in api.py state: # Remove previously recorded documentation errors from the item # (Any documentation errors will be recorded in the super class)
So it seems that this is a feature, not a bug.
In the second case (derived class with an additional parameter), the generator determines that the superclass constructor has a different signature, so no documentation is taken from the superclass. Not sure if this is something we want to change, I'll talk to Andreas about it.
We came to the conclusion that everything works as designed, so I'm closing this report.
Closed all bugs already shipped with a release.
